Stock Movements Around U.S. Elections
This project analyzes how the VIX and SPY (S&P 500 ETF) prices changed around U.S. presidential elections from 2000 to 2020.

Table of Contents
Installation
Usage
Results
License
Installation
Clone the Repository

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/price-movements-analysis.git
cd price-movements-analysis
Set Up a Virtual Environment (Optional)

bash
Copy code
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
Install Dependencies

bash
Copy code
pip install pandas yfinance matplotlib seaborn
Usage
Run the Analysis Script

bash
Copy code
python analyze_prices.py
This will generate:

election_price_movements.csv
election_trends.png
vix_comparison.png
correlation_heatmap.png
Results
CSV File: Contains VIX and SPY prices two months before, one month before, one month after, and two months after each election.
Visualizations:
Line Plot: Trends of VIX and SPY around elections.
Bar Chart: Comparison of VIX before and after elections.
Heatmap: Correlation between price movements.
